        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 24 at 5:07PM CDT by NWS Mobile AL</headline>
        <description>At 506 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles east of Brooklyn, or 15 miles north of Wiggins, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
New Augusta and Beaumont.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
